race.comment: QUIETLY ARROGANT (12) Capitalist gelding who raced without luck in his two-year-old season at Group and Listed level. Given a lengthy spell and ready to explode after the two fast trials. Hard to hold out. SHADY THINKER (7) struck trouble shortly after the start and forced to cover plenty of ground in the run when fifth over this trip at Rosehill. Rawiller stays aboard and gets his chance with the right run. TUNED (2) slick fresh gelding who bounced off his two good trials with a well-supported victory over this trip at Rosehill. Has a few hurdles to overcome today but nevertheless stays in the mix. DASHING RUPERT (8) has come back well this time in and no shock to see him finish over the top of these third-up. Value prospect who can turn the tables on his stablemate. SOCIABLE (14) gone to a new level after the lengthy break and not to be overlooked after the big win when circled the field at Wyong in weaker grade. Maps well and can surprise some of his more fancied rivals.
